issue.title: Feature/views
issue.body:
* The logic for all the questions have been tested and implement for views
* Animation injectors have been added

The main part left for front end is to build all the question fragments, and then to interact with the backend

The most notable thing is that matchr's design is now showcased (see [here](https://github.com/Harvard2017/matchr/blob/feature/views/app/src/main/java/com/matchr/data/Matchr.kt))

We will be able to change every question type, text, interaction, etc with this one klass

issue.title: Interface
issue.body: This adds the basic interface for the front end data flow
